{"id":17794,"title":"First documented case of human infection with ovine Shiga-toxin-producing Escherichia coli serotype O52:H45.","abstract":"We report a concurrent case of infection with non-O157 Shiga-toxin-producing Escherichia coli (STEC) strain in an 8-month-old child. Laboratory and epidemiological investigations indicated child exposure to contaminated sheep meat following the Muslim feast of sacrifice (Eid al-Adha). Microbiological and molecular typing confirmed that the ovine strain O52:H45 (stx1+, eae-, hlyA-) was the causal agent. This is the first documented case of human infection to this STEC serotype. ","date":"2014-06-06","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24849211","annotations":[{"name":"Escherichia coli","weight":0.720698,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Escherichia_coli"},{"name":"Sheep","weight":0.701811,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sheep"},{"name":"Muslim","weight":0.657982,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muslim"},{"name":"Oxygen","weight":0.612781,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oxygen"},{"name":"Meat","weight":0.606798,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meat"},{"name":"Epidemiology","weight":0.604587,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Epidemiology"},{"name":"Human","weight":0.602129,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human"},{"name":"Pathogen","weight":0.582424,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pathogen"},{"name":"Molecule","weight":0.460732,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Molecule"},{"name":"Infection","weight":0.45604,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infection"},{"name":"Microbiology","weight":0.334694,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microbiology"},{"name":"Contamination","weight":0.298818,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Contamination"},{"name":"Serotype","weight":0.1